# Quality Goals: [PROJECT_NAME]

## Propósito

Documentar QUÉ TAN BIEN debe el sistema cumplir sus requisitos, usando atributos de calidad con scenarios medibles.

> Objetivo: Especificar atributos de calidad (performance, security, usability, etc.) priorizados en tres niveles (Critical, Important, Desirable).

---

## Priority 1: Critical

| Quality Goal | Scenario |
|--------------|----------|
| [Attribute]  | Every [action] must [result] |
| [Attribute]  | Every [action] must [result] |
| [Attribute]  | Every [action] must [result] |

**Ejemplo:**
| Quality Goal | Scenario |
|--------------|----------|
| Correctness  | Every product price is correctly calculated in cart |
| Security     | Payment data is encrypted end-to-end |
| Reliability  | 99.9% of transactions process without error |

---

## Priority 2: Important

| Quality Goal | Scenario |
|--------------|----------|
| [Attribute]  | [Action] must complete within [time/measure] |
| [Attribute]  | System must handle [load] |
| [Attribute]  | User must complete [action] in under [time] |

**Ejemplo:**
| Quality Goal | Scenario |
|--------------|----------|
| Performance  | Product search returns results in under 2 seconds |
| Scalability  | System handles 10,000 concurrent users |
| Usability    | New user completes registration in under 3 minutes |

---

## Priority 3: Desirable

| Quality Goal | Scenario |
|--------------|----------|
| [Attribute]  | [Nice-to-have scenario] |
| [Attribute]  | [Nice-to-have scenario] |

**Ejemplo:**
| Quality Goal | Scenario |
|--------------|----------|
| Performance  | Mobile app loads products in under 1 second on 4G |
| Flexibility  | New payment methods can be added without code changes |

